<Layout title="Capital Gains Tax When Selling Your Home in Brisbane 2026 | Daniel Gierach Property" description="What Brisbane home sellers need to know about capital gains tax, the main residence exemption, the 50% CGT discount, and partial exemptions when selling in 2026.">

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do I pay capital gains tax when I sell my home in Brisbane?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "In most cases, no. If the property has been your main residence for the entire time you owned it, you are entitled to the full CGT main residence exemption and pay no capital gains tax on the sale. Exceptions apply if you have ever used the property to produce income, such as renting it out or claiming a home office deduction."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is the 50% CGT discount and how does it apply to property sales in Queensland?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "If you have owned a property for more than 12 months and the property does not qualify for the full main residence exemption, you may be entitled to a 50% discount on the capital gain. This means only half the gain is added to your assessable income in the year of sale. The discount applies to individuals and trusts but not companies."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What happens to CGT if I rented out part of my home in Brisbane?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "If you have rented out a portion of your main residence, the CGT exemption is reduced proportionally. The exempt portion is calculated based on the percentage of the property used as your main residence during your ownership period. You should obtain independent tax advice before selling if you have ever received rental income from any part of your home."
      }
    }
  ]
}
</script>

<article style="background:var(--color-surface-0);min-height:100vh;">

